text: Tomoe Zenimoto Hvas (born 1 June 2000) is a Norwegian swimmer. He competed in the men's 50 metre butterfly at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. He comes from Bærum, and has a Norwegian father and Japanese mother; also residing in Japan from 2007 to 2010. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Bærum Category:Norwegian people of Japanese descent Category:Norwegian male swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Youth Olympic gold medalists for Norway Category:Male butterfly swimmers Category:Male backstroke swimmers
